part of the model, where the noise\ncan be correlated with the variables corresponding to the linear part. We\nanalyze two real datasets via our method and compare our results with those\nobtained by using previous approaches. We conclude this paper with a discussion\non some possible extensions of our approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Feb 2021 17:59:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Mar 2021 18:38:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 31 Jul 2021 14:35:14 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 03:05:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-02"}
